# Coding standards


## Change discipline

- Change only what the task requires. Avoid drive-by refactors, unrelated files, and scope creep.
- Every line in a diff should serve the request. Prefer small, reviewable changes.

## Style and consistency

- Match existing naming, imports, structure, and documentation level in the file you edit.
- Reuse existing helpers instead of duplicating logic.
- Prefer clear control flow over deep nesting and one-off special cases.


## Static web (`static/*.js`, `static/*.css`, `static/*.html`)

- Keep UI consistent with existing spacing, typography, and color in `static/styles.css`.
- Avoid inline secrets; call server endpoints that read env on the backend.

## Dependencies

- Prefer well-maintained libraries. Before adding a dependency, confirm it is actively maintained and free of known critical issues.
